Paper: hep-th/9511189

Date: 1995-11-27

Title: The Three-Dimensional BTZ Black Hole as a Cylindrical System in

Four-Dimensional General RelativityAuthors: Jos\'e P.S. Lemos, Vilson T. Zanchin

Comments: Latex, 9 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D53 (1996) 4684-4686

It is shown how to transform the three dimensional BTZ black hole into a fourdimensional cylindrical black hole (i.e., black string) in general relativity.This process is identical to the transformation of a point particle in threedimensions into a straight cosmic string in four dimensions.